Discover the Spirit of Wildwood

Uncover the story behind our handcrafted spirits and explore the delicious world of Wildwood in our downloadable “Look Book” inside, you’ll find:

  • In-depth details on our award-winning spirits: From our flagship bourbon, The Dark Door, to our innovative wine-finished Whiskies, learn about the unique character of each bottle.
  • The “farm to distillery” philosophy: Discover our commitment to sourcing the finest, locally-grown ingredients from Washington state farms.
  • Tasting notes and pairing suggestions: Get expert advice on how to savor the distinct flavors of each Wildwood spirit, along with recommendations for perfect food pairings.

Our awards

We think our spirits are best-in-class, but don’t just take our word for it– we’ve accumulated a collection of shiny accolades from some of the world’s top spirits competitions to prove it!

The best craft spirits in Washington state

In the spirit of farmers from colonial times, who maximized local crops by making distillates from excess fruit and grain, we source nearly all of our ingredients from local farms. Nearly all of the produce used for distilling at Wildwood Spirits Co. — from cereal grains (corn, barley, and wheat) to Braeburn apples, to Douglas fir– is grown in Washington state. All our spirits are handcrafted in small batches in Bothell and Ballard Washington.
